member.name: P:Symbol.EMDK.Xamarin.ProfileManager.IsPreviousRequestPending
member.summary: This method tells whether the previous process profile request is pending or not. If the previous request is pending, you can't submit the next request until the current request completes and calling the process profile method will return error.
member.returns: boolean - Returns whether the previous process profile request is pending or not.

member.name: M:Symbol.EMDK.Xamarin.ProfileManager.ProcessProfile(System.String,Symbol.EMDK.Xamarin.ProfileManager+PROFILE_FLAG,Org.W3c.Dom.IDocument)
member.param: profileName - Name of the profile. ex: 'Profile1'.

profileFlag - ProfileManager.PROFILE_FLAG If the profileFlag is set to SET, and if the given profile is not available in the EMDKConfig.xml, it will look for valid profile in extraData argument and if present, the profile will be added to the internal XML volatile repository and also applied to the device. If the profile is present in the EMDKConfig.xml, it will be applied to the device. If profileFlag is set to GET and if the profile is present in the internal repository, it will be returned in extraData.
This can be used to provide data for processing action.
member.summary: Processes the given profile based on the data provided and the flag and return status of the action.
